	"system": {
		"description": {
			"value": "<p><strong>Materials:</strong> You require a snakes' tongue and either a bit of honeycomb or a drop of sweet oil.</p><p><em>You place a severed snake's tongue on your lips and offer a suggestion to a group of creatures, magically making your words sound appealing to them.</em></p><p><strong>Control Spell</strong></p><p>You suggest a specific course of action that the creatures believes they could finish within 24 hours.</p><p>The targets must be able to hear and understand you. This spell cannot compel someone to do something they would not normally consider doing. If a character could not influence a creature to do something with a persuasion skill check, the suggestion spell will not work either.</p><p><strong>[[/save wisdom]]{Wisdom Save}</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Failure:</strong> The target is &amp;reference[Charmed] by you. While charmed, they make your suggested course of action an immediate priority. If the suggested course of action leads the target or one of their allies to physical harm, or is about to lead them to harm, the spell ends. Targets will generally eat and take care of themselves, but only as much as is needed to follow the suggested course of action.</p></li><li><p><strong>Success:</strong> No effect.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Upcasting:</strong> When you cast this spell using a 7th-level spell slot, the duration is 10 days. When you use an 8th-level spell slot, the duration is 30 days. When you use a 9th-level spell slot, the duration is a year and a day.</p><p><em>You can also specify conditions that will trigger an action during the duration. For example, you might suggest that a group of knights give money to the first beggar they meet. If the condition isn't met before the spell expires, the activity isn't performed.</em></p>",
